As Indian students look beyond national borders for their higher education, countries like the UK are increasingly coming under their radar, offering numerous educational and career opportunities. While the country offers a host of trending programs, a field gaining immense popularity among Indian students is the Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech).

Read the blog to learn about program details, popular universities, admission requirements, courses, scholarships and job options offered in the country.

Why Study B.Tech in UK?

Students choose to study B.Tech in the UK for a variety of reasons that extend beyond the classroom, such as:

  • Quality Education: The UK houses some of the highest-ranking universities globally. As per the QS World University Rankings 2022, the University of Cambridge ranks at No. 3, and the University of Oxford stands at No. 5 globally.
  •  Global Recognition of the Degree: The degrees awarded by UK universities are recognised globally, enhancing students' career prospects in the global job market.
  • Diversity and International Exposure: Studying in the UK provides international students with a diverse and multicultural environment. As per the UKCISA (UK Council for International Student Affairs), over 450,000 students studied in the country for the 2019-2020 academic year.
  • Research Opportunities: The country invests heavily in research and development, giving students advanced research opportunities, especially those in the technical field of study.
  • High Employability Rate: The UK has a robust job market for engineering graduates. Some of the popular companies hiring B.Tech graduates are Google, Dyson, Amazon, Facebook, Deloitte, Samsung, etc.
  • Post-Study Work Visa: In a significant boost to international students, the UK government reintroduced the two-year post-study work visa in 2020. This allows graduates to stay in the UK and find work after their studies, increasing their chances of gaining international work experience.
  • Scholarships: According to the British Council, UK universities and the government offer thousands of scholarships, grants, and bursaries to international students every year to reduce financial stress.

B.Tech in UK: Admission Requirements

The eligibility for B.Tech programs in UK universities generally includes:

  • Academic Qualifications: Students should have completed 10+2 from a recognised board with Chemistry, Physics, and Mathematics as compulsory subjects
  • English Language Proficiency: In order to study in the academic institutes of the UK, international students must provide proof of their English through language proficiency tests like IELTS, TOEFL, or PTE
  • Entrance Exams: While many UK universities accept direct applications, some require students to take university-specific or international entrance exams like SAT or ACT

FAQ

What is the duration of a B.Tech program in the UK?
A Bachelor of Technology (B.Tech) degree in the UK is a full-time program with three years of duration. However, if a student opts for a sandwich course, which includes a year in industry or study abroad, the duration could extend to four years.
What are the admission requirements for a B.Tech program in the UK?
The admission criteria vary from institution to institution. However, applicants planning to apply for study B.Tech in the UK are expected to have good grades in their secondary school education, especially in the relevant subjects. Some universities may also require specific A-Level subjects or their equivalent.
What are some of the fields of study available for a B.Tech in the UK?
B.Tech degrees in the UK cover a wide range of technical and vocational areas, including engineering (mechanical, civil, electrical, etc.), computer science, information technology, biotechnology, aviation technology, and more.
What job prospects are available for students after completing a B.Tech degree in the UK?
B.Tech graduates in the UK can find employment in industries related to their field of study. This could be in various sectors such as technology, engineering, manufacturing, biotech, and more.
How much does it cost to pursue B.Tech in the UK?
The cost of studying in the country varies from institute to institute and generally includes tuition fee and living expenses. The approximate annual tuition fee for B.Tech in UK ranges between 24,500-44,000 GBP.
